Executive Profile
Marcus C. Rowland CPAFounder and Senior Managing Director, IOG Capital, LPAgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 7 Board Members in 7 different organizations across 10 different industries.See Board Relationships65--
Background

		Mr. Marcus C. Rowland, also known as Marc, CPA, is the Founder of IOG Capital, LP. serves as Senior Managing Director. Mr. Rowland serves as a Manager of Infinity Resources LLC. He is a seasoned oil and gas corporate executive, director and investment manager with over 40 years of experience in all aspects of upstream and midstream business segments. He is considered a leading industry expert in energy mergers, acquisitions, divestitures, public securities transactions ... and derivatives facilities. Mr. Rowland served as President and Chief Financial Officer of Frac Tech Services, LLC and FTS International, Inc. (formerly Frac Tech International, LLC) from November 1, 2010 to May 2011. He served as the Chief Executive Officer at FTS International, Inc. from May 2011 to November 2012. He served as the President and Chief Financial Officer of FTS International Services, LLC from November 1, 2010 to May 2011. Previously, he served as the Chief Financial Officer of Chesapeake Energy Corporation from 1993 to October 29, 2010 and served as its Executive Vice President of Finance from 1998 to October 29, 2010, Senior Vice President from 1997 to 1998 and Vice President of Finance from 1993 to 1997. He worked at Chesapeake Energy Corporation for 18 years. He served as Chief Operating Officer of Anglo-Suisse, LP from 1990 to 1992 where he was assigned to the White Nights Russian Enterprise, a joint venture of Anglo-Suisse, LP and Phibro Energy Corporation, a major foreign operation which was granted the right to engage in oil and gas operations in Russia. He has been the Chairman of SilverBow Resources, Inc. since September 26, 2016. He serves as a Member of Advisory Board of EDF Trading North America, LLC. Mr. Rowland serves as a Director of United Way of Central Oklahoma. He serves as a Member of Executive Council at Cohesive Capital Management, L.P. He serves as a Director of Post Oak Bank, N.A. He has been a Director of Omni Water Solutions, Inc. since April 22, 2013 and Mitcham Industries Inc. since September 9, 2015. He serves as a Director of United Guar LLC. He served as an Independent Director of Warren Resources, Inc. from December 2012 to March 4, 2016. He served as a Director of Chesapeake Midstream GP LLC, General Partner of Access Midstream Partners, L.P. from January 2010 to May 21, 2011. He served as a Director of First Commercial Bank. He has won numerous awards for transactions and has received recognition by Institutional Investor as Energy CFO of the Year. Mr. Rowland is a 1975 graduate of Wichita State University.Read Full Background




